%% Camunda 8 — Data-Flow Diagram
%% Shows four key data journeys through the system.
%% Renderable with any Mermaid-compatible viewer (GitHub, VS Code, etc.)

%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
%% Journey 1: Process Definition Deployment
%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Dev as Developer / Modeler
    participant GW as Gateway<br/>(REST / gRPC)
    participant Auth as Auth Layer
    participant Broker as Broker
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant State as State Store<br/>(RocksDB)
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant RExp as RDBMS Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch /<br/>OpenSearch
    participant DB as RDBMS
    participant Operate as Operate
    participant Tasklist as Tasklist

    Note over Dev,Tasklist: 🔵 Journey 1 — Deploy a Process Definition

    Dev->>GW: Deploy BPMN resource<br/>(REST POST /v2/deployments<br/>or gRPC DeployResource)
    GW->>Auth: Authenticate & authorize
    Auth-->>GW: ✅ Allowed
    GW->>Broker: BrokerDeployResourceRequest<br/>(routed to partition 1)
    Broker->>Engine: DEPLOYMENT:CREATE command
    Engine->>Engine: Parse & validate BPMN<br/>(bpmn-model)
    Engine->>State: Store ProcessDefinition
    Engine->>Log: Write DEPLOYMENT:CREATED event
    Engine->>Log: Write PROCESS:CREATED event
    Log->>CExp: Export DEPLOYMENT + PROCESS records
    CExp->>ES: Bulk index to<br/>process-definition index
    Log->>RExp: Export DEPLOYMENT + PROCESS records
    RExp->>DB: INSERT into<br/>process_definition table
    Note over Operate,Tasklist: Webapps query secondary storage
    Operate->>ES: Search process definitions
    Tasklist->>ES: Search startable processes

%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
%% Journey 2: Process Instance Execution
%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client as Client App
    participant GW as Gateway<br/>(REST / gRPC)
    participant Broker as Broker
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant State as State Store
    participant Worker as Job Worker
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch
    participant Operate as Operate

    Note over Client,Operate: 🟢 Journey 2 — Execute a Process Instance

    Client->>GW: Create process instance<br/>(REST POST /v2/process-instances<br/>or gRPC CreateProcessInstance)
    GW->>Broker: BrokerCreateProcessInstanceRequest
    Broker->>Engine: PROCESS_INSTANCE_CREATION:CREATE
    Engine->>State: Create instance state
    Engine->>Log: PROCESS_INSTANCE:ACTIVATED
    Engine->>Log: PROCESS_INSTANCE:ELEMENT_ACTIVATING<br/>(start event)
    Engine->>Log: PROCESS_INSTANCE:ELEMENT_ACTIVATED<br/>(start event)

    Note over Engine,Log: Engine advances through BPMN elements

    Engine->>Log: JOB:CREATED<br/>(for service task)
    Engine->>State: Store Job record
    Log->>CExp: Export all events
    CExp->>ES: Index process instance,<br/>flow nodes, jobs
    Operate->>ES: Query running instances

    Note over Worker,GW: Job Worker activates & completes job

    Worker->>GW: ActivateJobs (gRPC stream<br/>or REST POST /v2/jobs/activation)
    GW->>Broker: BrokerActivateJobsRequest
    Broker->>Engine: JOB_BATCH:ACTIVATE
    Engine->>Log: JOB:ACTIVATED
    Engine-->>Worker: Activated job<br/>(via gateway)

    Worker->>Worker: Execute business logic

    Worker->>GW: CompleteJob<br/>(with result variables)
    GW->>Broker: BrokerCompleteJobRequest
    Broker->>Engine: JOB:COMPLETE
    Engine->>State: Update job + variables
    Engine->>Log: JOB:COMPLETED
    Engine->>Log: VARIABLE:CREATED<br/>(result variables)

    Note over Engine,Log: Engine continues to next element(s)

    Engine->>Log: PROCESS_INSTANCE:ELEMENT_COMPLETING<br/>(end event)
    Engine->>Log: PROCESS_INSTANCE:COMPLETED
    Log->>CExp: Export completion events
    CExp->>ES: Update instance state<br/>to COMPLETED

%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
%% Journey 3: User Task Lifecycle
%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch
    participant TL as Tasklist
    participant User as End User
    participant GW as Gateway<br/>(REST)
    participant Broker as Broker

    Note over Engine,Broker: 🟠 Journey 3 — User Task Lifecycle

    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:CREATING<br/>(engine hits user task element)
    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:CREATED
    Log->>CExp: Export USER_TASK records
    CExp->>ES: Index user task<br/>(state: CREATED)

    User->>TL: Open Tasklist UI
    TL->>ES: Search user tasks<br/>(filtered by assignee / candidate)
    ES-->>TL: Task list
    TL-->>User: Display tasks

    User->>TL: Claim task
    TL->>GW: POST /v2/user-tasks/{id}/assignment
    GW->>Broker: BrokerAssignUserTaskRequest
    Broker->>Engine: USER_TASK:ASSIGN
    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:ASSIGNED
    Log->>CExp: Export assignment
    CExp->>ES: Update task assignee

    User->>User: Fill in form / provide data

    User->>TL: Complete task
    TL->>GW: POST /v2/user-tasks/{id}/completion
    GW->>Broker: BrokerCompleteUserTaskRequest
    Broker->>Engine: USER_TASK:COMPLETE
    Engine->>Log: USER_TASK:COMPLETED
    Engine->>Log: VARIABLE:CREATED<br/>(form output)

    Note over Engine,Log: Engine advances process<br/>past user task

    Log->>CExp: Export completion
    CExp->>ES: Update task state<br/>to COMPLETED

%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
%% Journey 4: Export Record Pipeline
%% ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Engine as Engine
    participant Log as Log Stream
    participant ExDir as Exporter Director<br/>(Broker)
    participant CExp as Camunda Exporter
    participant RExp as RDBMS Exporter
    participant ES as Elasticsearch /<br/>OpenSearch
    participant DB as RDBMS
    participant Search as Search Client<br/>(Abstraction)
    participant Svc as Service Layer
    participant Operate as Operate
    participant Tasklist as Tasklist
    participant Optimize as Optimize

    Note over Engine,Optimize: 🟣 Journey 4 — Export Record Pipeline

    Engine->>Log: Append record<br/>(any ValueType × Intent)

    Note over Log,ExDir: Exporter Director reads<br/>from log position

    ExDir->>CExp: record (position N)
    CExp->>CExp: Handler selection<br/>(83 handlers by ValueType)
    CExp->>CExp: Transform to<br/>ES/OS document
    CExp->>ES: Bulk index request<br/>(HTTP)
    ES-->>CExp: Ack
    CExp->>ExDir: Update exported position

    ExDir->>RExp: record (position N)
    RExp->>RExp: Handler selection<br/>(42 handlers by ValueType)
    RExp->>RExp: Transform to<br/>DB model
    RExp->>DB: INSERT / UPDATE<br/>(JDBC / MyBatis)
    DB-->>RExp: Ack
    RExp->>ExDir: Update exported position

    Note over ES,Optimize: Webapps read from secondary storage<br/>(eventually consistent)

    Operate->>Search: Search process instances
    Search->>ES: HTTP query
    ES-->>Search: Results
    Search-->>Operate: ProcessInstanceEntity[]

    Tasklist->>Search: Search user tasks
    Search->>DB: JDBC query<br/>(if RDBMS mode)
    DB-->>Search: Results
    Search-->>Tasklist: UserTaskEntity[]

    Optimize->>ES: Analytics queries<br/>(aggregations)
    ES-->>Optimize: Aggregated data
